NAME
       recon - Reconnaissance tool with support for port scanning, subdomain enumeration, and more

SYNOPSIS
       python3 recon --mode <mode> [options] --ip <IP> --p <start-end>

DESCRIPTION
       A fast and modular reconnaissance tool written in Python that performs common scanning tasks.

       Supported modes include:
           portscan     - Scan a range of ports on a target IP
           subenum      - Enumerate subdomains for a target domain
           dirbust      - Discover hidden paths/directories on a website (planned)

OPTIONS
       -ip, --ip_address <IP>
              Target IP address or domain to scan

       -p, --port_range <start-end>
              Port range to scan (e.g., 20-80)

       -w, --workers <int>
              Number of worker threads (default: 10)

       -t, --timeout <float>
              Timeout per socket connection in seconds (default: 1)

       -s, --stealth
              Run in stealth mode (suppress output, useful for silent scanning)

       --mode <string>
              Mode of operation (e.g., portscan, subenum). Required.

EXAMPLES
       Scan ports 1-1000 on 192.168.1.1 with 50 workers:
           python3 recon --mode portscan -ip 192.168.1.1 -p 1-1000 -w 50

       Subdomain enumeration on example.com:
           python3 recon --mode subenum -ip example.com

